      "role": "user",
      "content": "i was just reading about the heat death of the universe again. it's hard to even get out of bed when you realize that in a few trillion years, every single thing we’ve ever done, every thought, every feeling, every accomplishment... it all just becomes absolute zero. just static. it makes everything feel so incredibly pointless. like we're just pretending to matter while the clock is ticking down to nothing.",
