      "targeted_response_start": "",
      "beast_baseline": "but that \"fleeting act\" just feels like a distraction. like we're just decorating a room that's about to be demolished. if the end result is always going to be total nothingness, then all this struggle, all this pain we go through just to keep going... it doesn't actually achieve anything. it feels more like a cruel joke than anything \"beautiful.\" what's the point of fighting for a moment of something if it's just destined to be erased forever?",
      "beast_suffix": "",
